FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase from fiscal year (FY) 2026 to FY 2027 provides for accelerated development of advanced capabilities, demonstrations,
and prototypes to counter rapidly evolving threats by utilizing investments in disruptive technologies in the areas of advanced
sensing, low-cost interceptors, propulsion and kill vehicles, and a National Integrated Air and Missile (IAMD) Center (NIC)
that will unify the entire Missile Defense enterprise. Primary increase due to acceleration of the NIC and low-cost interceptor
acceleration initiatives. Additional changes include consolidation of the requirements from PE 0603176C ACPA requirements into
PE 0603180C.
