Title: Detect, Analyze and Mitigate Intrusions                                                                                            0.000          0.000       2.086
                                                                                                                           Articles:         -              -           -
Description: Cybersecurity capabilities/technology and policies that are dedicated to detecting, preventing, and resolving
intrusions. The key Detect, Analyze, and Mitigate Intrusions activities include:
- Cyber Continuity of Operations: Actions taken to ensure the continued viability and resiliency of Information Systems (IS) and
networks when confronted by all-hazards risk. Ensures that cyber operations maintain function after a disaster.
- Cyber Threat Analysis: The examination of the potential threat to include the threat's capability and intent; tactics, techniques,
and procedures; and equipment and organization. This also includes operational activities associated with threats to include red-
teaming and blue-teaming.
- Cybersecurity Network Operations: Operational and organizational elements that leverage tools and technical capabilities for the
day-to-day operations and defense of DoW networks. This includes all Cybersecurity Service Provider personnel and activities.
- Federal Incident Response Centers: Government focal points for dealing with computer-related incidents affecting federal civilian
agencies. The centers provide a means for federal civilian agencies to work together to handle security incidents, share related
information, and solve common security problems.
- Forensics and Damage Assessment: Forensically sound and accredited tools and methods to conduct analysis of a cyber
incident, criminal and malicious cyber activity, or electronic evidence to determine the scope and extent of any consequences,
including cost, and attribute the event to a particular attack type, threat vector, and when possible, group or individual. This
includes all forensics across the full range of military operations, and damage assessment activities associated with exfiltration
from Defense Industrial base Companies.




