Title: Ground Systems & Fire Control                                                                                                     301.120     390.062        778.497
                                                                                                                            Articles:         -           -              -
Description: The Ground Systems and Fire Control enables USNORTHCOM's command, control, and operations of the GWS
as part of the Missile Defense System. Ground Systems and Fire Control include the GFC, GCN, GNI, IDTs, and GSS. The GFC,
with nodes at FGA and the Missile Defense Integration and Operations Center in Colorado Springs, Colorado, plans midcourse
engagements and provides the Warfighter with a human-in-control interface for decision-making and command execution. The
GCN serves as the fire control network for the GWS and connects it to the broader Missile Defense System, while the GNI
provides a secure platform for real-time cyber integration and rapid response to cyber threats. IDTs, (2) located at FGA, (2) VSFB,
California, (1) Eareckson Air Station, Alaska, and (1) Fort Drum, New York, enable secure communication between the GFC and
in-flight interceptors. The GSS, comprising the Launch Support System and Missile Field/Launch Site Components at FGA and
VSFB, provides the hardware and software interfaces between the GFC and interceptors.

Recurring efforts include:
- Collect and analyze operational reliability, availability, maintainability, and testability data in order to support USNORTHCOM in
management of the interceptor fleet and development of fleet-maintenance strategies.
- Collect and analyze flight, ground, and cyber testing data in order to implement software and hardware updates, improvements,
and fixes to address test findings.
- Conduct design trade studies and engineering analyses to inform development.
- Conduct analysis of design performance countering the allocated threats.
- Conduct activities to support achieving Knowledge Points and milestone technical review entrance/exit criteria.
- Approve parts, materials, and process requirements.
- Conduct incremental delivery of the development, security, and operations software factory for continuous delivery and
integration of software updates.
- Continue future Ground Systems capability development incorporating a mixed fleet of Ground Based Interceptors and Next
Generation Interceptors.
- Continue PA-IDT detailed design activities.

Specific and/or unique accomplishments to each FY are as follows:

FY 2026 Plans:
- Complete Ground Test-13 post-test analysis.
- Field Ground Systems upgrades to USNORTHCOM.

