 is the Government's partner for day-to-day operation and sustainment of the GMD Weapon System alongside USNORTHCOM. While the Government maintains
 overall weapon system integration responsibilities and authority, the SITR contractor assumes a supporting role by aiding with GMD Weapon System integration, GMD
 contributions to Missile Defense System enterprise-level integration, and GMD requirements verification.

 The GMD BSC was awarded to Northrop Grumman in September 2021, and the EKV Sustainment Contract (ESC) was awarded to Raytheon Missile Systems in June
 2023. The Ground Based Interceptor Integration and Test acquisition was awarded to The Boeing Company via SITR, in July, 2025. These contracts are intended
 primarily to ensure fleet viability until the replacement Next Generation Interceptors are fielded. These contractors maintain the existing fleet, perform service life
 extensions, execute repairs, and develop software.

 GMD also uses MDA Consolidated Support contracts for engineering and technical support; studies, analyses, and evaluations; and management and professional
 services to GMD functional organizations and program offices. With a focus on achieving small-business goals, MDA is leveraging existing MDA Consolidated Support
 contracts and will utilize MDA competitively awarded new contracts to acquire future years Advisory and Assistance Services support.

 Other Enabling GMD Acquisition Strategies are budgeted for in PE 0604887C Test and PE 0604874C IHLD.




