Title: Missile Defense System - Next: Upgraded UEWR Algorithms                                                                            0.000       0.000          11.000
                                                                                                                           Articles:         -           -               -
Description: The project to upgrade the UEWR software is a critical element of the MDA mission to defend the United States
against evolving ballistic missile threats in all phases of flight. The UEWR software upgrades are part of the Advanced Object
Classification (AOC) project that will be fielded at all five UEWRs. AOC is a software development effort that incorporates
Machine Learning and new algorithms for classification of threat objects tracked by the UEWRs. AOC significantly improves
the efficacy of the UEWRs in the midcourse phase of the Missile Defense mission by reducing the number of false alarms and
increasing the accuracy of lethal object identification. Improved accuracy in identification of lethal objects will lead to more
efficient use of Ground-Based Interceptors. The AOC project encompasses the development, integration, delivery, test, and
fielding of improved classification capabilities to all five UEWRs.

