Description: The U.S Navy has developed and is testing the Advanced Capability Build (ACB) 20 Combat System, Aegis BL
10.x and AN/SPY-6(V)1, which is the combat system for Flight III DDGs. Initially Aegis BMD 6.x integrates Aegis BMD 5.1.2
capability with ACB 20, to include AN/SPY-6(V)1 requirements. BMD 6.x exploits the advanced capabilities of AN/SPY-6(V)1,
including improvements to Search, Track and Engagement, including discrimination, raid defense and expanded threat space.
This improved performance will enable Missile Defense System element utilization of AN/SPY-6(V)1 data for remote engagements
and will supplement deployed assets with simultaneous multi-mission capabilities (e.g. IAMD). AMDR will support a force-level
(multi-asset) approach to raid defense and enables U. S. Navy ships to have a greater stand-off range from threat environments.
BMD 6.x follow-on improvements will include introduction of Sea-Based Terminal Increment 3 and catch-up to all capabilities
resident in BMD 5.x.

Recurring Accomplishments:
- CIDS, IDS and, all supporting engineering documents and plans.
- Conduct design studies and concepts supporting development and integration.

