B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026        FY 2027
Description: The Next Generation Interceptor Development program will develop, integrate, test, and deliver a Next Generation
Interceptor for Homeland Defense, meeting the USNORTHCOM Operational Needs for Homeland Defense. The Next Generation
Interceptor consists of an integrated boost vehicle/multiple kill vehicle payload capable of surviving both natural and hostile
environments while countering the allocated threats.

Recurring efforts include:
- Conduct the interceptor design and development to include completion of design trade studies and engineering analyses.
- Conduct analysis of design performance countering the allocated threats.
- Conduct activities to support achieving KPs and milestone technical review entrance/exit criteria.
- Conduct parts testing, including radiation/suitability testing in support of final design.
- Conduct Parts, Materials, and Processes Control Board review and approval.
- Conduct incremental delivery of the Development, Security, and Operations software factory for continuous delivery and
integration of Next Generation Interceptor software updates.
- Conduct independent analysis and provide unbiased and objective advice and recommendations on Next Generation Interceptor
technical issues and development challenges through the GMD Technical Direction Agent.
- Development of PSE to support AUR emplacement and in-silo maintenance.
- Development of Next Generation Interceptor High Fidelity Models and Simulations Computer in the Loop Hardware in the Loop
hardware and software representing the integrated AUR design.
- Continue pre-production planning and related logistics life cycle evaluation.
- Develop and deliver incremental software to support multiple GMD Integrated Development and Execution.
- Develop and deliver incremental software capability release updates.

Specific and/or unique accomplishments to each FY are as follows:

FY 2026 Plans:
- Complete integrated AUR design.
- Complete KP #2, which includes sub-assembly qualifications, verification of AUR performance using verified models, and
completion of propulsion and sensor performance testing (planned in the FY 2025 President's Budget (PB) request).
- Generate evidence for KP #3, which includes live sequence demonstrations, confirmation of AUR supportability, software, and
completion of subsystem qualification (planned in the FY 2025 PB25 request).
- Complete boost vehicle qualification testing.
- Complete payload [Mission Support Vehicle (MSV) and Kill Vehicle (KV)] qualification testing.
- Complete payload (MSV and KV) software Formal Qualification Testing.


