Note
Increase from fiscal year (FY) 2026 to FY 2027 provides:
- Vessel maintenance in accordance with next scheduled in-port cycle as well as upgrading Sea Based X-Band Radar (SBX) hardware and software required to counter
the increased threat vector.
- Initiation of Model Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) by creating initial models for SBX radar behavior, antenna mount, and functional representation validation.
- Initiation of SBX Gallium Nitride (GaN) Transmit Receive Integrated Microwave Modules (TRIMM) upgrades to mitigate obsolescence and improve radar performance.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The SBX is an advanced X-Band Radar capable of mid-course acquisition, tracking, discrimination, and hit-assessment of missile threats. The SBX radar is mounted
on a mobile, ocean-going, semi-submersible platform, enabling it to cover any region of the globe. The SBX supports the Missile Defense System Homeland Defense
mission by tracking and discriminating sophisticated intercontinental ballistic missile threats.

The SBX operates at sea for the Homeland Defense mission and supports Missile Defense System flight and ground test. The SBX is located in a Pacific port when
maintenance is required. The SBX maintains vessel certifications for operations at sea and software compatibility with the Missile Defense System.




