(2) Operations & Sustainment (O&S): The Contractor Logistics Support IDIQ contract was awarded on November 1, 2017 for O&S, logistics, spares management, and
associated support of fielded radar systems. The SBX program has awarded TOs for continued O&S of the XBR aboard the SBX since the IDIQ was awarded with the
most recent being the award of FY 2025 - FY 2026 support (HQ0862-21-F-0002) on October 31, 2024, for continued O&S support through October 31, 2026.

(3) Mission Integration: The SBX product office holds a Mission Integration contract to fully integrate all aspects of the SBX program across all payloads to ensure
Homeland Defense and Space Domain Awareness mission readiness. The Mission Integration contract (HQ0862-25-C-0001) is a competitively awarded, Woman-
owned Small Business effort to maintain mission readiness 24 hours a day, 7 days a week for 365 days a year that was awarded on October 25, 2024, with a total PoP
through October 24, 2029, if all option periods are exercised.

The Navy's MSC maintains contracts for SBX-1 Vessel Management and Operations; Offshore Supply Vessel; and Security. The SBX-1 vessel was officially
transitioned and transferred to the U.S. Navy on December 22, 2011. Since then, MSC has been responsible for ensuring vessel readiness, vessel lifecycle
management and maintenance/repair, availability and operation of the Operational Support Vessel, transportation and vessel logistics support, security services, and
technical SME support for SBX-1 vessel systems. MSC manages all aspects of contract planning, award, and execution for these services. The MDA maintains
financial responsibility for all SBX-1 support and provides funding for these services via Military Interdepartmental Purchase Requests.




