D. Acquisition Strategy
The Missile Defense System Targets Program's acquisition strategy for Network / System Certification and Accreditation employs MDA's Consolidated Support for
Advisory and Assistance Services (A&AS). This strategy consists of contract actions to industry for: a) engineering and technical support; b) studies, analyses, and
evaluations; and management and professional services to MDA functional organizations and program offices. With a focus to achieve Small Business goals, MDA is
leveraging existing contracts and will competitively award new contracts to meet MDA's A&AS support.




