D. Acquisition Strategy
Acquisition strategy for the Defense of Guam consists of contract actions to industry, and agreements with Department of War organizations and Federally Funded
Research and Development Centers to develop, demonstrate, and field a Missile Defense System on Guam. MDA is leveraging existing programs of record with
existing and planned contracts. Major contributors include Aegis Guam Weapon System and AN/TPY-6 Radar; contributing capabilities support the Aegis Guam
System.




